- if Site.by_user(current_user).any?
  .col-md-3= render 'side'
%div{class: Site.by_user(current_user).any? ? 'col-md-9' : ''}
  .welcome
    = logo_big
    %h3 Welcome to <span class="hermes-title">Hermes</span>
  .explain
    %p
      To set up Hermes for your website, add the following code to your pages
      just before the ending
      %code &lt;/body&gt;
      tag and <b>before</b> your page scripts:
    .embed-element
      %pre#embed_static
        &lt;script src="#{asset_url('hermes.js')}"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
      %button.btn.btn-default.copy-element.btn-xs{:'data-clipboard-target' => "embed_static"}
        %i.fa.fa-files-o
        copy
    %p or you can dinamically import it via JavaScript:
    .embed-element
      %pre#embed_dynamic
        (function(d,l,s){s=d.createElement('script'),l=d.scripts[0];s.src='#{asset_url('hermes.js')}';l.parentNode.insertBefore(s,l)}(document));
      %button.btn.btn-default.copy-element.btn-xs{:'data-clipboard-target' => "embed_dynamic"}
        %i.fa.fa-files-o
        copy
    %p
      Then
    %p.text-center
      = link_to '#new-site-modal', class: 'btn btn-primary btn-lg', :'data-toggle' => 'modal' do
        %i.fa.fa-plus
        Add new site
  .explain
    %p
      Once you added a site, you can add as many messages as you wish to it: they will be shown to your visitor until they dismiss them.
    %p
      You can decide, for every single message:
    %ul
      %li the publishing time frame
      %li the visualization order (for multiple messages on one page)
      %li the layout type (broadcast message or tooltip bound to a specific page element)
